description:
&lt;p&gt;A new opportunity has arisen to join our friendly, dedicated team and applications are invited for the post of Consultant in General Medicine with Specialist Interest accommodated. This post will be based at The West Cumberland Hospital, Whitehaven. The post involves out-patient and in-patient duties and a regular commitment to both in-reach into the medical admissions unit and on-call for general medicine. Any sub-specialist interest would be welcomed and supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants must have full registration with the GMC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be coming to join a committed and experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact, Dr Paul Mead, Consultant in Renal Medicine, Nephrology:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul.Mead@ncic.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relocation assistance of up to £8,000 may be available for successful applicants moving to the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post currently attracts a discretionary recruitment premium of up to 10% (based on basic salary)per annum.&lt;/strong&gt;This is pensionable, payable for up to 4 years and is reviewed by the Trust on an annual basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
